RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUNCAN IDAHO stalked the early pace, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole and took over in the three path past the quarter pole, raced clear midway on the turn and was kept alert through the lane. HARLEY SIOUX chased inside, angled outward toward the top of the lane, lugged in through the stretch and was outfinished later yards. ALL ROADS TO DENIS broke a step slow then picked up the chase, rounded the turn about the three path and came along for third in later yards. WINDSOR'S STAR chased outside, raced in the five path on the turn and showed little in the lane. BIG BAD BRASS chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail then flattened in the lane. B. J. MOOSE set a pressured pace inside, was met at the rail past the quarter pole, dropped back midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. MYLASHURRAH saved ground.

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow break,chased,3p turn,along 3rd later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Harley Sioux
ENTRY.OWNER: Straughn William E and Thacker Daniel

ENTRY.NAME: B. J. Moose
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met rail past 1/4,weakened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Duncan Idaho

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 15200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE NOVEMBER 20, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since November 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,5 00, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUCHACHO MACHO raced with the early pace two deep, took the nod into the backstretch and kept the edge over Mi Gusto Es from that point, drew clear approaching the five sixteenths pole, came under pressure toward the far turn and held well with steady handling. UNCAPTURED KING rounded the first turn in the four path, bid past the half mile pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and settled for second. ELVIRUS was bumped at the break then saved ground, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the stretch. MI GUSTO ES came away awkwardly and made contact with Elvirus, rated a slim lead inside but was met into the backstretch, gave chase from that point, dropped back toward the five sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened in the lane. SPRING THE BEAST stalked the early pace from the three path but showed little response through the backstretch. INDIANA RED raced in the five path the first turn and never factored. MAKE THE WAY CLEAR raced well off the pace and never factored. MONGOLIAN HERO saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Elvirus
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,saved ground,chased 3/8,3p far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Uncaptured King
ENTRY.OWNER: Murdock Stephen and Marceda John A

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 13100. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOC ELM gave chase and dueled to the front in the three path approaching the head of the lane, drew clear past the eighth pole and was steadily handled to late stretch. ROCKING TO HOME chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail and dueled through the stretch for second. JEFFERSON SECURITY chased, raced in the three path on the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. BEAR'S ESTATE chased through the backstretch, raced close in the four path on the turn then flattened the final sixteenth. SPECTACULO eased to the outside and gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn and could only improve his position. TICKLING SPRINGS dropped well back and saved ground. HE'S ON THE LINE was hustled to a clear lead past the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, was caught at the rail approaching the eighth pole and gave way in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: He's On the Line
ENTRY.OWNER: Sperling Nancie S and Racanelli Mark Joseph
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled clear past 1/2,caught rail nearing 1/8,gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Bear's Estate
ENTRY.OWNER: Wilson Rayan and Knoblauch Michelle R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 91. Starter Allowance Purse 21700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE MAY 20, 2021. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since March 20 Allowe d 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAYJAYDEE rated a clear pace inside, came under pressure toward the quarter pole, widened at the rail on the far turn and was kept sharp in the lane. VELVET GHOST stalked from the three path, gave chase approaching the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and dueled through the stretch for second. WELLING settled off the pace in the four path, gave chase toward the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. LOKOYA ROAD saved ground off the pace, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but flattened in the four path of the far turn. MASTER THIS saved ground early on, eased out with a bid into the backstretch but showed little response. AKINGISALWAYSKING raced off the rail then faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Jayjaydee
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated clear inside,pressured 1/4,rail turn,kept sharp lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 20, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Ra ces Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAE SAI PRINCESS took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and held well with steady handling. MISS WILD stalked off the rail, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and settled for second best. FLOATING BY saved ground off the pace, bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, eased out leaving the turn and held on for third. LIFE IN FLASH raced well off the pace about the four path on the first turn, started an outside bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. LIGHTFOOT MISS settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the stretch. STORMI CAT LADY raced well back in the three path the first turn, gave chase toward the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and passed rivals in the lane. EMMA AND I stalked from the three path, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole but flattened in the three path of the far turn. UPSY DAISY DO raced two deep on the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but showed little response. SO RED THE ROSE showed little response. SEEDS OF TIME saved ground off the pace and was through after a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Life in Flash
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace 4p,outside bid 7/16,passed rivals,even finish

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 19600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REVEIRS MINUTE tapered in and stalked two deep, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage four wide on the far turn, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and dueled clear later yards. KATALIMA settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase from the half mile pole, rounded the far turn in the five and six paths, left the turn widest and dueled through the stretch for second. RATIONALMILLENNIAL saved ground on the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced in the four path of the far turn, drifted leaving the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second while getting up for third. SEEMS TO WHISPER rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. RIVER REWARDS RVF raced with the pace inside, was met at even terms leaving the half mile pole and dueled from that point, contested the far turn at the rail and remained a factor to mid-stretch before weakening. BAYLIS STREET was hustled toward contention and stalked off the rail, drew to even terms into the backstretch and dueled from that point, remained a close factor to mid-stretch then weakened. COFFEE BEAN never factored and saved ground on the far turn. TIZBIT was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Seems to Whisper
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close off rail,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Baylis Street
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUSIN WINNIE stalked off the rail, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole and raced near the rail on the far turn, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and edged away later yards. TIMETOGETUP took over and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, was met mid-stretch and relented the final sixteenth. HESSICA broke inward and settled off the rail on the first turn, eased out leaving the turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. CHANGE THE WORLD was shuffled back early then closed the gap to stalk from the three path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. BREADMAN'S ROSEBUD saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, angled to the outside leaving the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. TIMELY SECRET saved ground, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. SHE'S MYBUDDYBUDDY was not a factor. BAYS CASTLE saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Cousin Winnie
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,rail far turn,up 1/16,edged away

ENTRY.NAME: Breadman's Rosebud

ENTRY.NAME: Hessica

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 41. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLOUD MOVER stalked two deep then took the lead leaving the three eighths pole, drew clear toward the quarter pole, widened at the rail on the far turn and was kept alert through the lane. TAPTAP exchanged contact with Trace Estate leaving the gate and saved ground racing well back, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, steadily improved in the four path of the far turn, left the turn outside and dug in to clear second the final yards. LAURA'S GRAND saved ground just off the pace, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and held on for third. LADY GANGSTER set the early pace inside, was met leaving the three eighths pole and gave chase from that point, but dropped back approaching the quarter, raced near the rail on the far turn and flattened inside the sixteenth pole. JUJU ON DA BEAT rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn in the three path and flattened in the lane. BANK CARD rounded the opening turn about the five path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. SUNSET QUEEN settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but exchanged light contact with Only Romance approaching the quarter pole and flattened stride. TRACE ESTATE exchanged contact with Taptap leaving the gate then saved ground and showed little response. ONLY ROMANCE saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, exchanged light contact with Sunset Queen approaching the quarter pole and flattened stride.

ENTRY.NAME: Taptap
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,saved ground,bid 7/16,4p far turn,clear 2nd late
